gomodel:SYNGO_4175  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: - Postembedding immunogold EM of adult rat cerebral cortex was performed using 254.2 anti-liprin2-antibody.\n\n- Fig5B-C: EM images show the expression of gold particles adjacent to the postsynaptic membrane.\n\n- Fig5E quantifies the distribution of gold particles relative to the postsynaptic membrane (value of 0). The high peak within 50 nm of the postsynaptic membrane is suggestive of liprin-alpha 2 being localized in close proximity to the postsynaptic membrane in the postsynaptic specialization.\n\n- Fig. 3: Double immunofluorescence experiments demonstrated localization of liprin-alpha 2 with the postsynaptic protein GRIP along dendrites.. Experimental description: Rat hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from hippocampi dissected from E18 rat embryos as described (Goslin and Banker, 1991)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4175" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

